cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with quad meshing algorithms and partitioning surfaces into quadrilateral regions. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper discusses visual results and compares the algorithm to state-of-the-art methods. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility as the paper deals with computing cross fields on curved surfaces. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper deals with meshing algorithms and producing visual results. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper discusses efficient methods for computing cross fields and trajectory of streamlines.
